 He disposed and
subjected his mind, or himself, to do the thing;
syn. مَهَّدَهَا لِفِعْلِهِ وَذَلَّلَهَا (Msb.)

 [He fulfilled, performed, kept, or was faithful to, the compact,
or covenant, and the promise]: act. part. n. وَفِىٌّ;
pl. أَوْفِيَآءُ. (Msb.)

